3.00	Shamar_Rinpoche	Shamarpa	Shamarpa (Tibetan: , Wylie: Zhwa-dmar-pa; literally, "Person (i.e. Holder) of the Red Crown"), also known as Shamar Rinpoche or more formally Kunzig Shamar Rinpoche is a lineage holder of the Karma Kagyu school of Tibetan Buddhism and the mind manifestation of Amitabha Buddha, He is traditionally associated with Yangpachen monastery near Lhasa.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3f/Shamarpa_1.jpg/220px-Shamarpa_1.jpg
